        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Improve managed child-task flow UX for long-running tasks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR improves the long-running Task Flow path for managed child-task spawns created via `sessions_spawn(taskFlow=...)`.\n\nIt turns the flow from a mostly internal state machine into a more user-facing and durable experience:\n\n- `sessions_spawn(taskFlow=...)` can create managed flows for child-task work\n- child task completion now automatically closes the parent managed flow\n- managed child-task flows now surface minimal user-visible progress notifications\n- noisy nonterminal progress updates are throttled/aggregated\n- blocked vs retryable failures now expose clearer next-action guidance\n- retryable managed child-task flows now have a real retry command/operation, not just hints\n\n## What changed\n\n### 1. Managed flow creation from `sessions_spawn`\n- add `taskFlow` support to `sessions_spawn`\n- link spawned child tasks to `parentFlowId`\n- mark the managed flow as waiting on the child task\n- persist enough launch metadata under `stateJson.launch` for later retries\n\n### 2. Auto-close managed flows on child completion\n- close managed flows when the tracked child task reaches a terminal state\n- propagate completion context into flow `stateJson`\n- preserve special cases like `cancelled`, `lost`, and `blocked`\n\n### 3. Minimal user-facing progress delivery\n- add start / waiting / terminal notifications for managed child-task flows\n- prefer direct requester delivery when possible, with existing fallback behavior otherwise\n- use idempotent per-flow revision delivery keys\n\n### 4. Throttling + guidance\n- debounce noisy nonterminal `queued/running/waiting` chatter for managed child-task flows when `notifyPolicy: \"state_changes\"`\n- keep first waiting notification and terminal/blocked updates immediate\n- expose lightweight resolution hints:\n  - `blocked` => `user_action_required`\n  - `failed` / `lost` => `retry_available`\n- surface `resolution` / `nextAction` in runtime + CLI flow views\n\n### 5. Real retry operation loop\n- add real retry entrypoints for eligible managed child-task flows\n- restrict retry to sane terminal states (`failed`, `lost`, `blocked`)\n- re-launch the child task and move the flow back into `waiting` / `wait_worker`\n- clear stale completion/error state and rewrite `waitJson`\n- expose retry in runtime (`runtime.taskFlow.retryChildTask(...)`)\n- expose retry in CLI:\n  - `openclaw tasks flow retry <lookup>`\n  - `flows show` prints `retryCommand: openclaw tasks flow retry <id>` when retryable\n\n## Notes\n\nI kept the scope intentionally tight and backward-compatible:\n\n- no large new delivery subsystem\n- throttling only applies to managed child-task progress chatter\n- blocked child completion now stays `blocked` rather than collapsing into generic `failed`\n- retry depends on persisted launch metadata, so older flows may not always be reconstructable\n- attachment-dependent child spawns are not yet fully reconstructable for retry\n\n## Validation\n\nPassed targeted tests across:\n\n- `src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts`\n- `src/plugins/runtime/runtime-taskflow.test.ts`\n- `src/tasks/task-flow-registry.test.ts`\n- `src/tasks/task-executor.test.ts`\n- `src/plugins/runtime/runtime-tasks.test.ts`\n- `src/commands/flows.test.ts`\n- `src/cli/program/register.status-health-sessions.test.ts`\n\nRepresentative commands used:\n\n```bash\npnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.config.ts \\\n  src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts \\\n  src/plugins/runtime/runtime-taskflow.test.ts \\\n  src/tasks/task-flow-registry.test.ts \\\n  src/tasks/task-executor.test.ts \\\n  src/plugins/runtime/runtime-tasks.test.ts\n\npnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.config.ts \\\n  src/tasks/task-executor.test.ts \\\n  src/plugins/runtime/runtime-taskflow.test.ts \\\n  src/commands/flows.test.ts\n\npnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.config.ts \\\n  src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts \\\n  src/cli/program/register.status-health-sessions.test.ts\n```\n\nI also ran targeted TypeScript checks while working through the series.\n\n## Caveat\n\nRepo-wide `tsgo` / `tsc` still surfaces a pre-existing unrelated issue in `src/gateway/server.config-apply.test.ts`. That issue is outside this Task Flow patch series.\n",
        "branch": "pr/taskflow-long-task-clean",
